=====
Why is MDM important?

Answer:

Eliminates duplicate & inconsistent data

Improves data quality and governance

Enables better analytics & decision-making

Supports regulatory compliance
===

Rules that decide which attribute value wins when multiple source records are merged.

Example:

Source priority

Most recent update

Longest value
=====
What is Match & Merge?

Answer:

Match: Identify duplicate records

Merge: Combine duplicates into a single golden record
====
What is Data Governance in MDM?

Answer:
Policies, roles, processes, and standards to ensure data accuracy, consistency, and ownership.

====
What are common Data Quality dimensions?

Answer:

Accuracy

Completeness

Consistency

Timeliness

